Python Machine Learning Environment Setup
This guide provides the steps to set up a standardized Python virtual environment for xFusionCorp Industries' machine learning projects.

Prerequisites
Ensure you are logged into the controlplane host and working within the /root/code/ directory.

Setup Instructions
1. Create the Virtual Environment
Navigate to the project directory and create a virtual environment named ml-env:

Bash
cd /root/code/
python3 -m venv ml-env
2. Activate the Environment
Activate the environment to begin installing packages:

Bash
source ml-env/bin/activate
3. Install Required Libraries
Install the core data science libraries using pip:

Bash
pip install numpy pandas scikit-learn matplotlib
4. Generate Requirements File
Save the list of installed packages and their versions to ensure environment reproducibility:

Bash
pip freeze > /root/code/requirements.txt
Verification
You can verify the setup by checking the files in your directory:

Check directory structure: ls -l /root/code/

Verify requirements file content: cat /root/code/requirements.txt
